.TH BASENAME(1),User Commands,BASENAME(1)

.SH NAME
basename - strip directory and suffix from a pathname

.SH SYNOPSIS
basename string [suffix]

.SH DESCRIPTION
basename prints the final component of string, with any trailing slashes removed.
If string is entirely slashes, a single slash is printed.
If string is empty, the output is implementation-defined.

If the optional suffix is given and is not identical to the remaining component
but does match as a trailing suffix, it is removed from the printed result.
It is not an error for suffix not to match.

The result is followed by a newline.

.SH EXAMPLES
$ basename /usr/bin/sort

 sort

$ basename /usr/local/include/stdio.h .h

 stdio

.SH EXIT STATUS
basename exits 0 on success, or 1 if no string operand is given.
